ğŸ“¬ Notification Service
A Node.js REST API to send notifications via Email, SMS, and In-App channels.

Built with Express, MongoDB, Twilio, and SMTP (Gmail).

ğŸš€ Features
âœ… Send notifications via:

Email

SMS

In-App

ğŸ“¥ Fetch notifications for a user (with optional filtering by type)

âœ… Mark In-App notifications as read

ğŸ”Œ RESTful API with clean, modular code

ğŸ—„ï¸ Persistent storage using MongoDB

ğŸ”— Easily integrable with any frontend or backend

ğŸ› ï¸ Setup & Installation
1. Clone the repository
bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/DEVanshDEVS/notification-service.git
cd notification-service
2. Install dependencies
bash
Copy
Edit
npm install
3. Configure environment variables
Create a .env file in the root directory:

env
Copy
Edit
PORT=3000
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/notification_service

# Email (Gmail SMTP example)
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=your_email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your_gmail_app_password

# Twilio
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=your_twilio_sid
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=your_twilio_auth_token
TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER=your_twilio_number
4. Start the server
bash
Copy
Edit
npm start
The server will run at:
ğŸ‘‰ http://localhost:3000

ğŸ“š API Endpoints
â¤ Send a Notification
POST /notifications

json
Copy
Edit
{
  "userId": "USER_ID_HERE",
  "type": "in-app", // or "email" or "sms"
  "message": "This is a test notification!"
}
â¤ Get All Notifications for a User
GET /notifications/users/:id/notifications

Optional Filter by Type:

ruby
Copy
Edit
/notifications/users/:id/notifications?type=in-app
â¤ Mark In-App Notification as Read
PATCH /notifications/:notificationId/read

ğŸ‘¤ User Management
Ensure user documents exist in MongoDB. Notifications are sent to these users.

Sample User Document
json
Copy
Edit
{
  "name": "Receiver",
  "email": "receiver@example.com",
  "phone": "+1234567890"
}
ğŸ§ª Example Requests
âœ… Send In-App Notification
bash
Copy
Edit
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/notifications \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"userId":"USER_ID_HERE","type":"in-app","message":"Hello from in-app!"}'
ğŸ“¥ Get All In-App Notifications
bash
Copy
Edit
curl http://localhost:3000/notifications/users/USER_ID_HERE/notifications?type=in-app
âœ… Mark Notification as Read
bash
Copy
Edit
curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3000/notifications/NOTIFICATION_ID/read
ğŸ“ Notes
âŒ Never commit your .env file to a public repository.

ğŸ“§ Gmail SMTP requires an App Password (not your login password).

ğŸ“± Twilio requires an active account and a verified sender number.

